===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|chosen|lang=enm}}, {{term|chesen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|ceosan|ċēosan|to choose, seek out, select, elect, decide, test, accept, settle for, approve|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|keusaną||to taste, choose|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|ǵews-||to taste, choose, enjoy|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|chose|lang=sco}}, {{term|chese||to choose|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|kese||to choose|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|kieze||to choose|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|kiezen||to choose|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|kiesen||to choose|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|kyse||to choose|lang=da}}, Norwegian {{term|kjose||to choose|lang=no}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|tjusa||to charm, allure|lang=sv}}, Icelandic {{term|kjósa||to choose, vote, elect|lang=is}}, Gothic {{term|𐌺𐌹𐌿𐍃𐌰𐌽||tr=kiusan|to test|lang=got}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|gusto|gustō|taste, sample|pos=verb|lang=la}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{enPR|cho͞oz}}, {{IPA|/tʃuːz/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/tSu:z/}}
* {{audio|en-us-choose.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|uːz}}
* {{homophones|lang=en|chews}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|chooses|choosing|chose|chosen}}

# To [[elect]].
#: ''He was '''chosen''' as president in 1990''
# To [[pick]].
#: ''I '''chose''' a nice, ripe apple from the bowl.''
# To [[decide]] to act in a certain way.
#: ''I '''chose''' to walk to work today.''

